This paper deals with issues related to physical-layer network coding, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of belief propagation (cs.SI) for decoding and the impact of modulation schemes (cs.MM) and channel coding (cs.CR) on the performance of PNC. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT, followed by cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, and cs.CR.
